Manufacturers and vendors seeking USDA approval to use the certification mark for an eligible biobased product must submit a USDA-approved application for each biobased product. A standardized application form and instructions are available on the USDA BioPreferred Program Web site (
http://www.biopreferred.gov
). The contents of an acceptable application are as specified in paragraphs (a)(1) through (a)(4) of this section.

Effective (date to be added after authority to collect fee is granted), applicants must submit an application fee of $500 with each completed application for certification. Instructions for submitting the application fee are available on the USDA BioPreferred Program Web site (
http://www.biopreferred.gov
), along with the application form and instructions.

A multi-color version of the certification mark is preferred. The certification mark colors to be applied will be stipulated in the “Marketing Guides” document available on the USDA BioPreferred Program Web site (
http://www.biopreferred.gov
).
